ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M] , IxOS/IxNetwork-FT [M]

DESCRIPTION

Which mode is being performed. All but create require the use of create - Create a new LDP interfacemodify - Modify an existing LDP interfacedelete - Delete the given LDP interface

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

Which mode is being performed. All but create require the use of the -handle option. Valid choices are: create - Create a new LDP interface modify - Modify an existing LDP interface delete - Delete the given LDP interface

Valid options are:

create

Create the specified LSP or FEC Pools/Ranges.

modify

Modify the given LSP.

delete

Delete the specified LSP.

DEFAULT

 None

-handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

The LDP handle.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

The LDP handle.

DEFAULT

 None

-return_detailed_handles

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This argument determines if individual interface, session or router handles are returned by the current command. This applies only to the command on which it is specified. Setting this to 0 means that only NGPF-specific protocol stack handles will be returned. This will significantly decrease the size of command results and speed up script execution. The default is 0, meaning only protocol stack handles will be returned.

DEFAULT

0

-egress_label_mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

This argument can be used to specify whether or not the same label will be used for all the FECs in the FEC range. It has any meaning only when the fec_type option is set to host_addr.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This argument can be used to specify whether or not the same label will be used for all the FECs in the FEC range. It has any meaning only when the fec_type option is set to host_addr.

Valid options are:

nextlabel

Next available label is assigned for each LSP.

fixed

The same label (increment from previous FEC range) is assigned for all LSPs in this FEC range.

imnull

Implicit null is used for all LSPs.

exnull

Explicit null is used for all LSPs.

DEFAULT

nextlabel

-fec_type

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

Note: this option cannot be modified with modify mode.

Valid options are:

ipv4_prefix

configure FECs to be advertised by the

host_addr

configure FECs to be requested of upstream peers, to be

vc

configure parameters for VC range associated with an LDP L2 VPN

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

Note: this option cannot be modified with modify mode. Valid choices are: ipv4_prefix - configure FECs to be advertised by the simulated router host_addr - configure FECs to be requested of upstream peers, to be used in download on demand advertising mode. vc - configure parameters for VC range associated with an LDP L2 VPN interface.

Valid options are:

ipv4_prefix

Configure FECs to be advertised by the simulated router.

host_addr

Configure FECs to be requested of upstream peers, to be used in download on demand advertising mode.

vc

Configure parameters for VC range associated with an LDP L2 VPN interface.

network_topology

Configure parameters for configuring a network topology.

DEFAULT

ipv4_prefix

-network_topology_type

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

The type of topology route to create.

Valid options are:

grid

This option configures a grid type network topology in network group.

mesh

This option configures a mesh type network topology in network group.

custom

This option configures a custom type network topology in network group.

ring

This option configures a ring type network topology in network group.

hub-and-spoke

This option configures a hub and spoke type network topology in network group.

tree

This option configures a tree type network topology in network group.

fat-tree

This option configures a fat tree type network topology in network group.

linear

This option configures a linear type network topology in network group.

DEFAULT

 None

Valid only when using IxTclNetwork.

1

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

Valid only when -mode is create/modify and -fec_vc_type is atm_cell or atm_vcc_1_1 or atm_vpc_1_1 or atm_vcc_n_1 or atm_vpc_n_1 and fec_type is vc. Valid only when using IxTclNetwork.

DEFAULT

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork-NGPF

Coded versus functional specification. If fec_type option is ipv4_prefix, the label_msg_type option must be mapping; if fec_type option is host_addr, the the label_msg_type option must be request. For "modify" mode, the fec_type option and label_msg_type option will not be updated for the lsp. When using the new IxTclNetwork API 5.30, the label_msg_type option is silently ignored. Only the fec_type option is used. DESCRIPTION

Which mode is being performed. All but create require the use of create - Create a new LDP interfacemodify - Modify an existing LDP interfacedelete - Delete the given LDP interface

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

Which mode is being performed. All but create require the use of the -handle option. Valid choices are: create - Create a new LDP interface modify - Modify an existing LDP interface delete - Delete the given LDP interface

Valid options are:

create

Create the specified LSP or FEC Pools/Ranges.

modify

Modify the given LSP.

delete

Delete the specified LSP.

DESCRIPTION

The LDP handle.

return_detailed_handles

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This argument determines if individual interface, session or router handles are returned by the current command. This applies only to the command on which it is specified. Setting this to 0 means that only NGPF-specific protocol stack handles will be returned. This will significantly decrease the size of command results and speed up script execution. The default is 0, meaning only protocol stack handles will be returned.

DEFAULT

0

egress_label_mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

This argument can be used to specify whether or not the same label will be used for all the FECs in the FEC range. It has any meaning only when the fec_type option is set to host_addr.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This argument can be used to specify whether or not the same label will be used for all the FECs in the FEC range. It has any meaning only when the fec_type option is set to host_addr.

Valid options are:

nextlabel

Next available label is assigned for each LSP.

fixed

The same label (increment from previous FEC range) is assigned for all LSPs in this FEC range.

imnull

Implicit null is used for all LSPs.

exnull

Explicit null is used for all LSPs.

DEFAULT

nextlabel

Coded versus functional specification. If fec_type option is ipv4_prefix, the label_msg_type option must be mapping; if fec_type option is host_addr, the the label_msg_type option must be request. For "modify" mode, the fec_type option and label_msg_type option will not be updated for the lsp. When using the new IxTclNetwork API 5.30, the label_msg_type option is silently ignored. Only the fec_type option is used. If the current session or command was run with -return_detailed_handles 0 the following keys will be omitted from the command response: fecproperty_handles, ldppwvpls_handles, ldpotherpws_handles, ldpvplsbgpad_handles

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

Coded versus functional specification.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

If fec_type option is ipv4_prefix, the label_msg_type option must be mapping; if fec_type option is host_addr, the the label_msg_type option must be request.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

For "modify" mode, the fec_type option and label_msg_type option will not be updated for the lsp.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

When using the new IxTclNetwork API 5.30, the label_msg_type option is silently ignored. Only the fec_type option is used.

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This argument determines if individual interface, session or router handles are returned by the current command. This applies only to the command on which it is specified. NOTES

IxNetwork-NGPF

Coded versus functional specification. If fec_type option is ipv4_prefix, the label_msg_type option must be mapping; if fec_type option is host_addr, the the label_msg_type option must be request. For "modify" mode, the fec_type option and label_msg_type option will not be updated for the lsp. When using the new IxTclNetwork API 5.30, the label_msg_type option is silently ignored. Only the fec_type option is used. If the current session or command was run with -return_detailed_handles 0 the following keys will be omitted from the command response: fecproperty_handles, ldppwvpls_handles, ldpotherpws_handles, ldpvplsbgpad_handles

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

Coded versus functional specification.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

If fec_type option is ipv4_prefix, the label_msg_type option must be mapping; if fec_type option is host_addr, the the label_msg_type option must be request.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

For "modify" mode, the fec_type option and label_msg_type option will not be updated for the lsp.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

When using the new IxTclNetwork API 5.30, the label_msg_type option is silently ignored. Only the fec_type option is used.
